events.objective: Join us to explore Chi Gong, a Chinese system of physical exercises and breathing control. Learn basic moves to enhance your energy, improve circulation, and achieve a balanced state of mind.

Embark on a full-day fly fishing adventure! You'll learn how to cast, retrieve, and handle fish responsibly. Get hands-on experience in fly tying and fish spotting, all while enjoying the natural beauty of the riverbank.

Discover the art and culture of tea ceremony. You'll experience the detailed process of tea preparation and understand the symbolism behind each step. This ceremony is more than just drinking tea; it's a practice of mindfulness and a celebration of aesthetics.
Come learn how to make your own tea blends for both flavor and health benefits. You'll be introduced to a variety of herbs, spices, and tea bases. You'll create your own blend to take home with you.

Learn the basics of aquaponics, a sustainable farming method combining aquaculture and hydroponics. You'll understand the ecosystem, set up requirements, and get hands-on experience in maintaining a small-scale aquaponics system.

This class will provide you with essential gardening techniques, from soil preparation to planting and pest control. Perfect for those who wish to develop a green thumb and cultivate their own gardens.

Do you live in a city but still want to grow your own food? This class will teach you how to use containers, balconies, and small spaces to grow vegetables. You'll go home with a potted vegetable to start your urban garden.

Learn the science and art behind the fermentation process. Discover how to ferment foods like kimchi, sauerkraut, and kefir safely. Understand the health benefits and walk away with a jar of your own fermented food.
This class dives into the history, types, and crafting methods of incense. You'll get hands-on experience in mixing different herbs, resins, and oils to create your own aromatic incense sticks.
Join us for a cozy afternoon of candle making. Learn about the different types of wax, wicks, and how to set a candle properly. Make and take home your own scented candle at the end of the class.

Discover the basics of herbal medicine, including the properties and uses of common herbs. This class will also guide you through the process of making simple herbal remedies like tinctures and balms.

In this class, you'll get a comprehensive introduction to raising chickens in your backyard. Learn about the types of chickens, coop designs, feeding, and routine care. Get hands-on experience with some feathery friends.

Join us for a walking tour identifying local herbs and their uses. Gain a basic understanding of plant families, terminology, and ethical wild harvesting. Learn to identify several useful plants and their potential applications.
events.tagline: A walk through nature's medicine cabinet.

events.objective: Discover the art and science of Matcha, the powdered green tea used in traditional Japanese tea ceremonies. Learn about its health benefits, history, and various grades. Prepare and taste Matcha in its traditional form.

Explore the local aquatic life with Martin, an experienced fisherman. This class teaches you how to identify common fish species, their habitats, and behavior. Learn the basics of sustainable fishing practices.
events.tagline: Know your fish, before you dish.

events.objective: Accompany Luke on a forest walk to identify trees and plants, both common and rare. Learn about different types of vegetation, their role in the ecosystem, and their uses in traditional and modern medicine.
events.tagline: Meet the greens in your neighborhood.

events.objective: In this introductory course, you'll dive into the fascinating world of beekeeping. Learn about bee behavior, colony structures, and the process of honey production. You will also learn the basics of setting up your own beehive.

Get hands-on experience in the art of whittling. Understand the basics of wood types, carving tools, and techniques. By the end of the class, you'll create your own small wooden figure. Ideal for anyone interested in woodworking.

Learn essential survival skills for wilderness adventures. Topics include building a fire, finding water, and basic navigation. Gain the confidence to handle unexpected situations in the great outdoors.
events.tagline: Survive and thrive in the wild.

events.objective: Learn how to cultivate food in unused public spaces. This unconventional approach to farming can make cities more sustainable and help combat food scarcity. Understand the legal aspects and community benefits.
events.tagline: Cultivate change, one seed at a time.

events.objective: Round Table is a dinner series that revolves around thought provoking questions and group discussion. The emphasis of Round Table is to encourage guests to connect with one another through storytelling and shared reflection. Highlighting up and coming chefs in Los Angeles, our goal is to create culinary experiences that reflect each chefs heritage and food journey. Round Table is an opportunity for chefs and dinner guests alike to share their stories and personal narratives. Join us as we spend an evening with chef David to embrace his take on Western and Japanese flavors with Californian seasonal produce and seafood.
events.tagline: A night of connection and storytelling through food.
events.isIncluded: Four-Course Farm to Table Meal, California wine pairings, non-alcoholic beverages
events.toBring: An open mind and an empty stomach!

events.objective: This Intro to Falconry is a once-in-a-lifetime opportunity to get up close and personal with birds of prey. You will be taught how to hold and fly trained birds in a natural setting, and you'll get ample time with the birds directly. You'll meet three species of birds, including a baby owl and a huge exotic hawk, and learn about falconry history, equipment, and raptor conservation. You'll aslo receive free professional quality photographs with the birds.
events.tagline: Up-close experience with birds of prey
events.isIncluded: Lesson on falconry, individual time holding and flying falcons, falconry glove, high quality photo with birds

events.objective: Early risers unite! Discover the local bird species in their natural habitats. Understand the importance of birds in the ecosystem and learn how to identify them by their calls and features.
events.tagline: Feather your knowledge, one bird at a time.

events.objective: Forest Therapy is a presence and mindfulness practice, inspired by the Japanese practice of Shin-rin Yoku, and is backed by scientific research that supports healing and wellness by immersion in forests or other natural environments. Participants at this event will be guided through a series of sensory invitations intended to help establish a connection to the present, to the body, and to the more than human world.
events.tagline: A recreational trip to the forest for relaxation and well-being

events.objective: In this class, you'll learn the basics of food fermentation, discover its health benefits, and how to safely ferment at home. We'll cover topics like sauerkraut, pickles, and kombucha. By the end, you'll be equipped to start your own fermentation projects.
events.tagline: Unlock the power of fermented foods!

events.objective: Embark on a morning trail run through Forest Park. Experience the beauty of nature in the early morning light while jogging through serene landscapes. This run is designed to boost your endurance and help you connect with nature. Suitable for all fitness levels.
events.tagline: Start your day right with a trail run.

events.objective: Learn the fundamentals of bouldering with an emphasis on technique and safety. This class will provide a thorough understanding of equipment use, grip techniques, and body positioning. It's an ideal starting point for anyone interested in rock climbing. Safety equipment will be provided.

Experience the tranquility of kayaking during sunset. As the sky paints itself with oranges and purples, you'll glide along the river, absorbing the peaceful atmosphere. This class covers basic paddling techniques and offers a unique way to unwind. No prior kayaking experience is needed.

This mountain biking class is tailored for beginners and focuses on building fundamental skills. You will learn about balance, gear shifting, and navigating various terrains. The objective is to instill confidence in off-road biking while prioritizing safety. Helmets and first-aid kits will be provided.

Begin your day with yoga in the heart of nature. This session aims to improve your flexibility, focus, and inner peace. Surrounded by the sights and sounds of the meadow, you'll engage in a variety of poses and breathing exercises. It's a perfect way to harmonize body, mind, and nature.

Embark on a hiking journey through the forest reserve to connect with nature and build your stamina. This hike is moderately challenging and provides breathtaking views of natural landscapes. Along the way, your guide will point out flora and fauna, enriching your knowledge about the forest ecosystem. Snacks will be provided.

Perfect for bird enthusiasts and nature lovers alike, this expedition takes you through the national park to observe indigenous and migratory birds. Learn about bird species, their habitats, and behaviors from an expert guide. Binoculars and bird identification books are provided. A light breakfast is included.

This class is tailored for beginners interested in rock climbing. Learn the basics of belaying, knot-tying, and climbing techniques under the supervision of a certified instructor. All safety measures are strictly observed. Equipment, including climbing shoes and harnesses, are provided.

Always wanted to try archery? This beginner's course will teach you the fundamentals, including stance, aim, and release. Your instructor will guide you through the basics and ensure a safe and enjoyable experience. Equipment is provided, and by the end of the session, you'll be hitting those targets!

Experience the joy of canoeing down a peaceful river. Learn basic paddling techniques, safety protocols, and on-water maneuvers. This class aims to give you a foundational understanding of canoeing, preparing you for future paddling adventures. Life vests and paddles are provided.

Rejuvenate your mind and body with an outdoor yoga session at the mountain top. The class includes breathing exercises, yoga postures, and guided meditation. Experience how the fresh mountain air enhances your yoga practice. A yoga mat is recommended, but not necessary.

Discover the wonders of the night sky in this star-gazing event. We'll start with a brief introduction about constellations and celestial bodies, followed by a telescope session. Explore the moon, planets, and distant galaxies as you've never seen them before. Light refreshments will be served.

Enhance your running skills with a trail running bootcamp. Navigate natural terrains, improve your pacing, and build stamina. The session will start with warm-ups and progress into running drills. The trails offer varying levels of difficulty to test your skills and endurance.

This class is designed to introduce you to the basics of backpacking, from choosing the right gear to trip planning. We'll take a short hike to a nearby campsite, set up tents, and discuss various outdoor survival techniques. This is the perfect class for those who are new to backpacking or need a quick refresher.
events.tagline: Carry your world on your shoulders.

events.objective: In this comprehensive workshop, you'll acquire the essential skills needed for winter survival. Learn how to build an emergency snow shelter, find and purify water, and recognize signs of frostbite and hypothermia. Knowledgeable instructors will guide you through various winter survival tactics, ensuring you're prepared for any situation.

Experience kayaking while observing local wildlife in their natural habitat. This guided tour will take you through calm lake waters, teaching you kayaking basics along the way. Keep your eyes peeled for birds, fish, and maybe even some larger mammals. We aim to provide a peaceful yet engaging outdoor experience.

Learn the basics of foraging and identifying wild edible plants. Our expert will guide you through the forest, teaching you how to safely gather and prepare plants for consumption. You'll learn which plants are safe to eat, their nutritional value, and how to incorporate them into meals.

Discover the art of bushcraftâ€”living in the natural environment with minimal modern amenities. Learn how to build a fire, construct a basic shelter, and make simple tools. This class provides hands-on training for those who want to delve deep into natural living.

You'll leave the class equipped with the confidence to handle basic medical situations in the wilderness.

This class will introduce you to the essentials of map reading and compass navigation. Gain hands-on experience while navigating a marked course. By the end, you'll be able to use a topographical map and compass effectively, ensuring you never lose your way.

Learn primitive and modern fishing techniques suitable for survival situations. This class will teach you how to catch fish without conventional gear, using methods like handlining and spearfishing. It's a great way to add another layer of self-sufficiency to your outdoor skills.

Master the art of fire-making using primitive and modern techniques. Learn how to identify the right kindling, how to build a fire lay, and how to maintain your fire safely. These are vital skills for anyone who wants to venture into the wilderness.

If you're new to rock climbing, this introductory course is perfect for you. Learn the basics of knot-tying, belaying, and climbing techniques in a controlled environment. After this course, you'll have the confidence and skills to try outdoor climbing.

Gear up for an adrenaline-pumping mountain biking session. This course will cover the essentials like bike setup, riding techniques, and trail etiquette. Ideal for beginners or those looking to sharpen their skills, you'll tackle various terrains under expert guidance.

Learn the skill of natural shelter building. Whether it's a temporary lean-to or a more elaborate debris hut, our expert will guide you through the process of creating a shelter from natural materials. A must-know skill for any outdoor enthusiast.
